<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 05 at 7:04PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of central Pittsburg
County through 730 PM CDT...
At 704 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles south of Blocker to 6 miles northwest of
Daisy. Movement was west at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Krebs...
Kiowa...                          Savanna...
Crowder...                        Alderson...
Blocker...                        Mcalester Regional Airport...
Blanco...                         Haileyville...
Pittsburg...                      Dow...
Bache...                          Featherston...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
